                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d82">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Memorandum.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1902-10-10">
                            <hi rend="italic">October 10, 1902</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>The request in the memorandum of the Belgian legation dated the 6th instant, that
                    the United States vessel at Cape Haitien be authorized to concert measures with
                    the Belgian consul there for the protection of common interests in the Bayeux
                    plantation, was communicated to the Navy Department.</p>
                <p>That Department wrote on the date above referred to, that instructions had been
                    issued to that end.</p>
            </div>
